---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Newsletter from '../components/Newsletter.astro';
---

<Base title="AfterChildren">
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="hero">
      <p class="hero__eyebrow">For parents whose children are grown</p>
      <h1 class="hero__title">
        You raised them.<br />
        <em>Now build yourself.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="hero__lede">
        Your adult children are not your retirement plan. They are not your healthcare plan. They are not your loneliness plan. AfterChildren is the unfiltered guide to the second half — for parents who refuse to be a burden, refuse to be invisible, and refuse to outsource their future.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FIVE PILLARS -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="pillars">
      <p class="pillars__eyebrow">The Five Sovereignties</p>
      <h2 class="pillars__title">Five things you have to build, in roughly this order.</h2>
      <div class="pillars__grid">
        <a href="/body" class="pillar" style="border-bottom: 0;">
          <div class="pillar__number">01</div>
          <h3 class="pillar__title">Body</h3>
          <p class="pillar__desc">The foundation. Everything else sits on it. The single highest-return decision in your 50s and 60s.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/money" class="pillar" style="border-bottom: 0;">
          <div class="pillar__number">02</div>
          <h3 class="pillar__title">Money</h3>
          <p class="pillar__desc">The fuel. Without it, nothing else is optional. The retirement math has to actually work — not "approximately" work.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/mind" class="pillar" style="border-bottom: 0;">
          <div class="pillar__number">03</div>
          <h3 class="pillar__title">Mind</h3>
          <p class="pillar__desc">The structure that holds the meaning. Purpose, marriage, friendship, cognition — built on purpose, not by default.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/legal" class="pillar" style="border-bottom: 0;">
          <div class="pillar__number">04</div>
          <h3 class="pillar__title">Legal</h3>
          <p class="pillar__desc">The walls. The protections against the worst outcomes. Five documents most people don't have.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/living" class="pillar" style="border-bottom: 0;">
          <div class="pillar__number">05</div>
          <h3 class="pillar__title">Living</h3>
          <p class="pillar__desc">The roof. Where and how you live for the next 30 years. The decision with the most variance and the least examination.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- IN-DEPTH ARTICLES (Tier 1 conversion engines) -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="articles">
      <p class="articles__eyebrow">In-depth</p>
      <h2 class="articles__title">The work, broken down.</h2>

      <a href="/legal/five-essential-documents-over-55" class="article-card">
        <span class="article-card__category">Legal · 13 min read · New</span>
        <h3 class="article-card__title">The Five Documents Every Adult Over 55 Needs (And Most People Don't Have)</h3>
        <p class="article-card__excerpt">The cornerstone article for the Legal pillar. What each document costs, what happens to your family without it, and the Saturday-morning execution plan to complete all five in one sitting.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/money/medicare-advantage-vs-medigap-2026" class="article-card">
        <span class="article-card__category">Money · 16 min read · New</span>
        <h3 class="article-card__title">Medicare Advantage vs Medigap: The Honest Comparison for 2026</h3>
        <p class="article-card__excerpt">The decision that locks in for life — and the marketing that obscures it. The five dimensions that actually matter, the 2026 rule changes, and the honest answer for most healthy 65-year-olds.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MANIFESTO CLUSTER -->
  <section class="page">
    <div class="articles">
      <p class="articles__eyebrow">The Manifestos</p>
      <h2 class="articles__title">The four founding essays.</h2>

      <a href="/manifesto" class="article-card">
        <span class="article-card__category">Manifesto · Pinned</span>
        <h3 class="article-card__title">The AfterChildren Manifesto</h3>
        <p class="article-card__excerpt">Why this site exists, what it stands for, and what it refuses to say. Read this first.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/manifestos/you-raised-them-now-build-yourself" class="article-card">
        <span class="article-card__category">Manifesto I · 14 min read</span>
        <h3 class="article-card__title">You Raised Them. Now Build Yourself.</h3>
        <p class="article-card__excerpt">The second half of your life is not a wind-down. It is a second build. Here is what to construct, in what order, and why most people get it backwards.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/manifestos/adult-children-not-retirement-plan" class="article-card">
        <span class="article-card__category">Manifesto II · 15 min read</span>
        <h3 class="article-card__title">The Hardest Truth: Your Adult Children Are Not Your Retirement Plan</h3>
        <p class="article-card__excerpt">The quiet assumption baked into millions of retirement plans — and the brutal math underneath why it fails. The hardest essay we have published.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/manifestos/moving-in-with-kids-fails" class="article-card">
        <span class="article-card__category">Manifesto III · 14 min read</span>
        <h3 class="article-card__title">Why Moving In With Your Kids Almost Always Fails</h3>
        <p class="article-card__excerpt">The 70% failure rate nobody warned you about. The three situations where it actually works. The math, the failure modes, and the alternative most parents do not consider.</p>
      </a>

      <a href="/manifestos/loneliness-after-kids-leave" class="article-card">
        <span class="article-card__category">Manifesto IV · 14 min read · New</span>
        <h3 class="article-card__title">The Loneliness After Kids Leave Is Real — And Solvable</h3>
        <p class="article-card__excerpt">Why the year after the last child leaves is the loneliest of most parents' adult lives — and why the structural fix that actually works has nothing in common with what every wellness publication is recommending.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Newsletter />
</Base>
